Implemented US-001 party state persistence hardening in [src/main.rs](/mnt/d/Projects/game/src/main.rs).

What changed:
- Added strict save compatibility validation for `campaign_parties` before deserialization.
- Required fields now include:
  - campaign-level: `selected_party_id`, `notice`, `parties`, `next_id`
  - per-party: `id`, `name`, `leader_hero_id`, `region_id`, `supply`, `speed`, `is_player_controlled`, `order`, `order_target_region_id`
- Loading now fails with explicit compatibility errors when party fields are missing, preventing lossy fallback/partial state mutation.
- Added tests:
  - roundtrip save/load preserves delegated `PatrolNearby` + target region exactly
  - missing party field causes compatibility failure and does not mutate runtime world state
- Updated save/load determinism test fixture to initialize `CampaignParties` up front (story-relevant drift fix).

